Although the consistency of the mode shapes can be evaluated by observing the modal shapes of the FE model and the test model, this comparison is only a qualitative analysis. Through the calculation of the MAC, the degree of relationship between the modal shapes of the FE model and the test model can be quantitatively determined, and thus a more objective evaluation can be given. The MAC values always lie between 0 and 1. The value of
